through which she could express

00:24:12.940 --> 00:24:14.420
it further, take the next step.

00:24:14.420 --> 00:24:19.080
And for her, that ended
up writing a novel.

00:24:19.080 --> 00:24:22.610
That has now been "New York
Times" number one bestseller

00:24:22.610 --> 00:24:24.280
for 83 weeks.

00:24:24.280 --> 00:24:24.780
You know?

00:24:24.780 --> 00:24:25.390
SPEAKER: Unbelievable.

00:24:25.390 --> 00:24:27.265
AMANDLA STENBERG: I'm
not saying that's going

00:24:27.265 --> 00:24:28.190
to happen to everyone.

00:24:28.190 --> 00:24:30.620
But find your own lane.

00:24:30.620 --> 00:24:32.120
But I feel like--

00:24:32.120 --> 00:24:32.720
I don't know.

00:24:32.720 --> 00:24:36.800
I really believe in the power
of expressing your activism

00:24:36.800 --> 00:24:38.634
through your
artistry, and this was

00:24:38.634 --> 00:24:40.300
such a beautiful
opportunity, because it

00:24:40.300 --> 00:24:43.449
was this like, synchronistic,
like, beautiful thing, where

00:24:43.449 --> 00:24:44.990
everything came
