in your professional career

00:26:57.800 --> 00:27:00.590
where you might have to change
a mannerism a little bit,

00:27:00.590 --> 00:27:03.440
and kind of juxtaposing that
with your actual environment

00:27:03.440 --> 00:27:05.060
from where you are back home?

00:27:05.060 --> 00:27:07.250
How are you able to
navigate through the waters

00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:10.228
and kind of live two
different personalities?

00:27:14.064 --> 00:27:15.026
[LAUGHING]

00:27:15.026 --> 00:27:17.322
SPEAKER: Challenge.

00:27:17.322 --> 00:27:18.780
AMANDLA STENBERG:
You know, I mean,

00:27:18.780 --> 00:27:23.980
I started going to that school
when I was 10 years old.

00:27:23.980 --> 00:27:28.950
So for me, for a long
time, I had this idea

00:27:28.950 --> 00:27:32.000
that there was something
wrong with code switching,

00:27:32.000 --> 00:27:33.900
that there was
something wrong with me

00:27:33.900 --> 00:27:39.210
for having kind of this
multi-faceted personality

00:27:39.210 --> 00:27:42.810
that shifted depending
on who I was around.

00:27:42.810 --> 00:27:45.605
And it kind of took me
until I was a bit older

00:27:45.605 --> 00:27:47.730
to understand that there's
nothing wrong with that,

00:27:47.730 --> 00:27:53.190
and that that's pretty natural,
considering the circumstances.

00:27:53.190 --> 00:27:58.020
I used to hate that I had
to make myself smaller

00:27:58.020 --> 00:28:01.680
or change who I was in
order to feel more accepted

00:28:01.680 --> 00:28:02.610
into that environment.

00:28:02.610 --> 00:28:07.740
But learning that language
of whiteness and privilege

00:28:07.740 --> 00:28:10.380
has actually been
really invaluable to me

00:28:10.380 --> 00:28:12.540
when it comes to
navigating Hollywood.

00:28:12.540 --> 00:28:14.280
Who would have thunk it?

00:28:14.280 --> 00:28:15.610
[LAUGHING]

00:28:15.610 --> 00:28:17.287
So it's a tool.

00:28:17.287 --> 00:28:19.120
You know, it's a tool
at the end of the day.

00:28:19.120 --> 00:28:21.660
I don't necessarily
look at it anymore

00:28:21.660 --> 00:28:23.820
as having to compromise myself.

00:28:23.820 --> 00:28:26.700
I also have kind of witnessed
this shift happening,

00:28:26.700 --> 00:28:31.920
where we are living in a culture
that is so transparently driven

00:28:31.920 --> 00:28:35.730
by black culture and by
blackness that I'm starting

00:28:35.730 --> 00:28:38.130
to notice that, even
in my spaces of work

00:28:38.130 --> 00:28:41.640
within my industry, if I show
up to that space authentically

00:28:41.640 --> 00:28:45.030
as myself, I seem to be
more accepted than I ever

00:28:45.030 --> 00:28:46.750
have been in the past.

00:28:46.750 --> 00:28:49.080
And there seems to
be this kind of push

00:28:49.080 --> 00:28:53.750
for an inclusivity that is new.

00:28:53.750 --> 00:28:56.400
And so I feel like
I have to compromise

00:28:56.400 --> 00:28:58.500
myself less and less.

00:28:58.500 --> 00:29:02.460
But I'm just more accepting of
all the different parts of me

00:29:02.460 --> 00:29:05.970
and the way that they
manifest in my mannerisms,

00:29:05.970 --> 00:29:08.520
or the way I talk.

00:29:08.520 --> 00:29:10.780
